To divide, multiply numerator and denominator by the conjugate of the denominator:

\[
\frac{3}{2-3i}\;\times\;\frac{2+3i}{2+3i}
=\frac{3(2+3i)}{(2-3i)(2+3i)}
=\frac{6+9i}{4+9}
=\frac{6+9i}{13}
=\frac{6}{13}+\frac{9}{13}i.
\]

To divide \(-4\) by \(3-2i\), multiply numerator and denominator by the conjugate of the denominator:

\[
\frac{-4}{3-2i}\;\times\;\frac{3+2i}{3+2i}
=\frac{-4(3+2i)}{(3-2i)(3+2i)}
=\frac{-12-8i}{3^2-(2i)^2}
=\frac{-12-8i}{9-(-4)}
=\frac{-12-8i}{13}
=-\frac{12}{13}-\frac{8}{13}\,i.
\]

\(-2-3i\over 4i\) can be simplified by multiplying top and bottom by \(-i\):

\[
\frac{-2-3i}{4i}\cdot\frac{-i}{-i}
=\frac{(-2-3i)(-i)}{4i(-i)}
=\frac{2i+3i^2}{-4i^2}
=\frac{2i-3}{4}
=-\tfrac34+\tfrac12\,i.
\]
